 of influential sociological theories of state formation, while showing how labor movements and other forms of popular mobilization shaped the origins of the regional states-system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aMiddle East Studies. 4aPolitics -- International Relations. 4aPolitics -- Middle East. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107042040 cprintz978080475372240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804768023?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804768023423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804768023/original  a978-3-11-070420-4  Stanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles